      • DeliveryClient

        public DeliveryClient(java.lang.String projectId)
        Initializes a new instance of the DeliveryClient class for retrieving content of the specified project.
        Parameters:
        projectId - The Project ID associated with your Kentico Cloud account. Must be in the format of an UUID.
        Throws:

      • DeliveryClient

        public DeliveryClient(java.lang.String projectId,
                      java.lang.String previewApiKey)
        Initializes a new instance of the DeliveryClient class for retrieving content of the specified project, and configures the preview API.

        An API key (which comes in the form of a verified JSON Web Token) provides read-only access to a single project. You can find the API keys for your project in the API keys section in the Kentico Cloud app.

        Parameters:
        projectId - The Project ID associated with your Kentico Cloud account. Must be in the format of an UUID.
        previewApiKey - The Preview API key configured with your Kentico Cloud account.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the Project id is invalid.
